## 4. Query Implementation Strategies (All Six Queries)\
\
The pseudocode below is implementation-oriented and mapped to MongoDB operators/indexes.\
\
### 4.1 Query 1 - AirBnB search (Portland, 2-day period, sorted by average rating)\
\
Goal: listings available for both days in a requested 2-day window, with listing details, sorted by rating desc.\
\
```javascript\
// Inputs: startDate, endDate (2-day period)\
// Indexes used: calendar \{city, listing_id, date\}, listings \{city, listing_id\}\
\
candidateListings = db.calendar.aggregate([\
  \{ $match: \{\
      city: "portland",\
      date: \{ $in: [startDate, endDate] \},\
      available: true\
  \}\},\
  // ensure both dates are available\
  \{ $group: \{\
      _id: "$listing_id",\
      availableDays: \{ $sum: 1 \}\
  \}\},\
  \{ $match: \{ availableDays: 2 \} \}\
])\
\
db.listings.aggregate([\
  \{ $match: \{ city: "portland", listing_id: \{ $in: candidateListings._id \} \} \},\
  \{ $project: \{\
      _id: 0, name: 1, neighborhood: 1, room_type: 1, accommodates: 1,\
      property_type: 1, amenities_raw: 1, price: 1, review_scores_rating: 1\
  \}\},\
  \{ $sort: \{ review_scores_rating: -1 \} \}\
])\
```\
\
### 4.2 Query 2 - Neighborhoods with no listings for a given month\
\
Goal: for all cities, find neighborhoods with zero active listings in a target month.\
\
```javascript\
// Inputs: monthStart, monthEnd\
// Indexes: neighborhoods \{city, neighborhood\}, calendar \{city, listing_id, date\}, listings \{city, listing_id\}\
\
activeNeighborhoods = db.calendar.aggregate([\
  \{ $match: \{\
      date: \{ $gte: monthStart, $lte: monthEnd \},\
      available: true\
  \}\},\
  \{ $group: \{ _id: \{ city: "$city", listing_id: "$listing_id" \} \} \},\
  \{ $lookup: \{\
      from: "listings",\
      let: \{ c: "$_id.city", l: "$_id.listing_id" \},\
      pipeline: [\
        \{ $match: \{ $expr: \{ $and: [\
          \{ $eq: ["$city", "$$c"] \},\
          \{ $eq: ["$listing_id", "$$l"] \}\
        ]\}\}\},\
        \{ $project: \{ neighborhood: 1, _id: 0 \} \}\
      ],\
      as: "listingInfo"\
  \}\},\
  \{ $unwind: "$listingInfo" \},\
  \{ $group: \{ _id: \{ city: "$_id.city", neighborhood: "$listingInfo.neighborhood" \} \} \}\
])\
\
db.neighborhoods.aggregate([\
  \{ $project: \{ _id: 0, city: 1, neighborhood: 1 \} \},\
  \{ $match: \{ $expr: \{ $not: \{ $in: [ \{ city: "$city", neighborhood: "$neighborhood" \}, activeNeighborhoods._id ] \} \} \} \}\
])\
```\
\
### 4.3 Query 3 - Salem "Entire home/apt" availability periods by month\
\
Goal: detect contiguous bookable intervals that satisfy per-day minimum nights.\
\
```javascript\
// Inputs: targetMonthStart, targetMonthEnd\
// Indexes: listings \{city, neighborhood,room_type\} (city+room_type filter),\
//          calendar \{city, listing_id, date\}\
\
listingIds = db.listings.find(\
  \{ city: "salem", room_type: "Entire home/apt" \},\
  \{ listing_id: 1, name: 1, _id: 0 \}\
).toArray()\
\
rows = db.calendar.find(\
  \{\
    city: "salem",\
    listing_id: \{ $in: listingIds \},\
    date: \{ $gte: targetMonthStart, $lte: targetMonthEnd \}\
  \},\
  \{ listing_id: 1, date: 1, available: 1, minimum_nights: 1, _id: 0 \}\
).sort(\{ listing_id: 1, date: 1 \}).toArray()\
\
// Post-processing per listing:\
// 1) scan consecutive available=true runs\
// 2) for each day in a run, keep day only if runLengthFromThatDay >= minimum_nights(day)\
// 3) merge remaining valid days into [from,to] ranges\
// 4) output listing name, month, from-to, min_nights\
```\
\
Comment: this query has sequence logic that is awkward to express purely in aggregation; a hybrid approach (indexed fetch + application pass) is clearer and easier to validate.\
\
### 4.4 Query 4 - Booking trend by month (Portland, March-August)\
\
Goal: total bookable nights per month for Portland "Entire home/apt", reusing query-3 availability logic.\
\
```javascript\
// Inputs: year, months = [03..08]\
// Reuse indexed fetch + run segmentation logic from Query 3\
\
for each month in [03..08]:\
  validIntervals = computeBookableIntervals(city="portland", roomType="Entire home/apt", month)\
  // Sum lengths of all valid intervals\
  totalBookableNights[month] = sum(interval.to - interval.from + 1)\
\
return [\{month, totalBookableNights\}, ...]\
```\
\
Operationally, we keep the interval computation in one reusable function so query 4 is just a loop and aggregation over query-3-style outputs.\
\
### 4.5 Query 5 - Booking trend by city: number of reviews in each December\
\
Goal: for each city, count reviews during December grouped by year.\
\
```javascript\
// Indexes: reviews \{city, listing_id, date\}\
\
db.reviews.aggregate([\
  // convert date string to date if needed\
  \{ $addFields: \{ d: \{ $toDate: "$date" \} \} \},\
  \{ $match: \{ $expr: \{ $eq: [ \{ $month: "$d" \}, 12 ] \} \} \},\
  \{ $group: \{\
      _id: \{\
        city: "$city",\
        year: \{ $year: "$d" \}\
      \},\
      review_count: \{ $sum: 1 \}\
  \}\},\
  \{ $sort: \{ "_id.city": 1, "_id.year": 1 \} \}\
])\
```\
\
### 4.6 Query 6 - Reminder to book again + other listings by same host in same city\
\
Goal: find reviewer/listing pairs with multiple reviews, check if listing is available in the same month as previous review, and include host's other city listings.\
\
```javascript\
// Indexes: reviews \{reviewer_id, listing_id, date\}, calendar \{city, listing_id, date\},\
//          listings \{host_id, city\}, listings \{city, listing_id\}\
\
repeatReviews = db.reviews.aggregate([\
  \{ $match: \{ reviewer_id: \{ $ne: null \} \} \},\
  \{ $addFields: \{ d: \{ $toDate: "$date" \} \} \},\
  \{ $group: \{\
      _id: \{ city: "$city", listing_id: "$listing_id", reviewer_id: "$reviewer_id" \},\
      review_dates: \{ $push: "$d" \},\
      review_count: \{ $sum: 1 \}\
  \}\},\
  \{ $match: \{ review_count: \{ $gt: 1 \} \} \}\
])\
\
for each group in repeatReviews:\
  for each priorReviewDate in group.review_dates:\
    monthStart, monthEnd = monthBounds(priorReviewDate)\
\
    wasAvailable = db.calendar.findOne(\{\
      city: group._id.city,\
      listing_id: group._id.listing_id,\
      date: \{ $gte: monthStart, $lte: monthEnd \},\
      available: true\
    \}) != null\
\
    listing = db.listings.findOne(\{ city: group._id.city, listing_id: group._id.listing_id \})\
\
    otherListings = db.listings.find(\{\
      city: listing.city,\
      host_id: listing.host_id,\
      listing_id: \{ $ne: listing.listing_id \}\
    \}, \{ name: 1, listing_url: 1, _id: 0 \}).toArray()\
\
    emit(\{\
      listing_name: listing.name,\
      listing_url: listing.listing_url,\
      description: listing.description,\
      host_name: listing.host_name,\
      reviewer_id: group._id.reviewer_id,\
      previously_booked: true,\
      month: YYYY_MM(priorReviewDate),\
      min_nights: lookupMonthMinNights(listing.city, listing.listing_id, monthStart, monthEnd),\
      max_nights: lookupMonthMaxNights(listing.city, listing.listing_id, monthStart, monthEnd),\
      available_in_same_month: wasAvailable,\
      other_host_listings_same_city: otherListings\
    \})\
```\
